{
  "stem": "2578.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Until the night of May the 7th, when we heard dull cannon sounds of explosions.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And we realized that something is-- something is going on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "We literally didn't dare to hope that this was the end.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Because the thought of the war to end was so remote for us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "We just couldn't believe that something like this could ever happen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Every one of us were resigned that I will be the next one to drop dead on the ground or on the bunk that I was laying.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "But nevertheless, about-- after midnight, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] inmates came running in, into the building, yelling that the gates are open, and the Germans left.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Now, in order to elaborate on it, I have to say our camp consisted of three-story-- of a three-story wooden building.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The barrack was a big, three-story wooden building.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was on the second or the third floor, I don't even remember anymore.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But on the ground floor were those who were still capable of walking around and so on.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Adjacent to our building was a brick building, where the German SS lived and slept.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And about midnight, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] May the 8th, those were walking around, from the ground floor, noticed that the gates from the camp were open.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the doors of this adjacent building, of this brick building, were open, and the Germans were running out.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So they realized that something is happening.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they came running, whoever was able-- capable of doing-- to tell us the good news that the Germans left.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We were not capable of doing anything about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
